<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n38166d"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n38" href="#n38166d">N38 (VI.B.32)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n38all.htm#n38166d"> 166(d)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Anpu ~</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">When the deceased had repeated the magical names of the doors of the Hall, he entered it and saw these gods arranged in two rows, twenty-one on each side of the Hall. At the end, near Osiris, were the Great Scales, under the charge of <mark>Anpu (Anubis)</mark>, and the monster Amemit, the Eater of the Dead, <i>i.e.</i>, of the hearts of the wicked who were condemned in the Judgment of Osiris. <small> E.A. Wallis Budge, <a name="BOD2" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#BOD2"><cite title="source">The Book of the Dead</cite></a> (1920) 23</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c08019b" href="c08all.htm#c08019b">VI.C.08:019(b)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
